1/* $NetBSD: ramfuc.h,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:33 riastradh Exp $ */

3#ifndef __NVKM_FBRAM_FUC_H__
4#define __NVKM_FBRAM_FUC_H__
5#include <subdev/fb.h>
6#include <subdev/pmu.h>
7
8struct ramfuc {
9 struct nvkm_memx *memx;
10 struct nvkm_fb *fb;
11 int sequence;
12};
13
14struct ramfuc_reg {
15 int sequence;
16 bool force;
17 u32 addr;
18 u32 stride; /* in bytes */
19 u32 mask;
20 u32 data;
21};
22
23static inline struct ramfuc_reg
24ramfuc_stride(u32 addr, u32 stride, u32 mask)
25{
26 return (struct ramfuc_reg) {
27 .sequence = 0,
28 .addr = addr,
29 .stride = stride,
30 .mask = mask,
31 .data = 0xdeadbeef,
32 };
33}
34
35static inline struct ramfuc_reg
36ramfuc_reg2(u32 addr1, u32 addr2)
37{
38 return (struct ramfuc_reg) {
39 .sequence = 0,
40 .addr = addr1,
41 .stride = addr2 - addr1,
42 .mask = 0x3,
43 .data = 0xdeadbeef,
44 };
45}
46
47static noinline struct ramfuc_reg
48ramfuc_reg(u32 addr)
49{
50 return (struct ramfuc_reg) {
51 .sequence = 0,
52 .addr = addr,
53 .stride = 0,
54 .mask = 0x1,
55 .data = 0xdeadbeef,
56 };
57}
58
59static inline int
60ramfuc_init(struct ramfuc *ram, struct nvkm_fb *fb)
61{
62 int ret = nvkm_memx_init(fb->subdev.device->pmu, &ram->memx);
63 if (ret)
64 return ret;
65
66 ram->sequence++;
67 ram->fb = fb;
68 return 0;
69}
70
71static inline int
72ramfuc_exec(struct ramfuc *ram, bool exec)
73{
74 int ret = 0;
75 if (ram->fb) {
76 ret = nvkm_memx_fini(&ram->memx, exec);
77 ram->fb = NULL;
78 }
79 return ret;
80}
81
82static inline u32
83ramfuc_rd32(struct ramfuc *ram, struct ramfuc_reg *reg)
84{
85 struct nvkm_device *device = ram->fb->subdev.device;
86 if (reg->sequence != ram->sequence)
87 reg->data = nvkm_rd32(device, reg->addr);
88 return reg->data;
89}
90
91static inline void
92ramfuc_wr32(struct ramfuc *ram, struct ramfuc_reg *reg, u32 data)
93{
94 unsigned int mask, off = 0;
95
96 reg->sequence = ram->sequence;
97 reg->data = data;
98
99 for (mask = reg->mask; mask > 0; mask = (mask & ~1) >> 1) {
100 if (mask & 1)
101 nvkm_memx_wr32(ram->memx, reg->addr+off, reg->data);
102 off += reg->stride;
103 }
104}
105
106static inline void
107ramfuc_nuke(struct ramfuc *ram, struct ramfuc_reg *reg)
108{
109 reg->force = true;
110}
111
112static inline u32
113ramfuc_mask(struct ramfuc *ram, struct ramfuc_reg *reg, u32 mask, u32 data)
114{
115 u32 temp = ramfuc_rd32(ram, reg);
116 if (temp != ((temp & ~mask) | data) || reg->force) {
117 ramfuc_wr32(ram, reg, (temp & ~mask) | data);
118 reg->force = false;
119 }
120 return temp;
121}
122
123static inline void
124ramfuc_wait(struct ramfuc *ram, u32 addr, u32 mask, u32 data, u32 nsec)
125{
126 nvkm_memx_wait(ram->memx, addr, mask, data, nsec);
127}
128
129static inline void
130ramfuc_nsec(struct ramfuc *ram, u32 nsec)
131{
132 nvkm_memx_nsec(ram->memx, nsec);
133}
134
135static inline void
136ramfuc_wait_vblank(struct ramfuc *ram)
137{
138 nvkm_memx_wait_vblank(ram->memx);
139}
140
141static inline void
142ramfuc_train(struct ramfuc *ram)
143{
144 nvkm_memx_train(ram->memx);
145}
146
147static inline int
148ramfuc_train_result(struct nvkm_fb *fb, u32 *result, u32 rsize)
149{
150 return nvkm_memx_train_result(fb->subdev.device->pmu, result, rsize);
151}
152
153static inline void
154ramfuc_block(struct ramfuc *ram)
155{
156 nvkm_memx_block(ram->memx);
157}
158
159static inline void
160ramfuc_unblock(struct ramfuc *ram)
161{
162 nvkm_memx_unblock(ram->memx);
163}
164
165#define ram_init(s,p) ramfuc_init(&(s)->base, (p))
166#define ram_exec(s,e) ramfuc_exec(&(s)->base, (e))
167#define ram_have(s,r) ((s)->r_##r.addr != 0x000000)
168#define ram_rd32(s,r) ramfuc_rd32(&(s)->base, &(s)->r_##r)
169#define ram_wr32(s,r,d) ramfuc_wr32(&(s)->base, &(s)->r_##r, (d))
170#define ram_nuke(s,r) ramfuc_nuke(&(s)->base, &(s)->r_##r)
171#define ram_mask(s,r,m,d) ramfuc_mask(&(s)->base, &(s)->r_##r, (m), (d))
172#define ram_wait(s,r,m,d,n) ramfuc_wait(&(s)->base, (r), (m), (d), (n))
173#define ram_nsec(s,n) ramfuc_nsec(&(s)->base, (n))
174#define ram_wait_vblank(s) ramfuc_wait_vblank(&(s)->base)
175#define ram_train(s) ramfuc_train(&(s)->base)
176#define ram_train_result(s,r,l) ramfuc_train_result((s), (r), (l))
177#define ram_block(s) ramfuc_block(&(s)->base)
178#define ram_unblock(s) ramfuc_unblock(&(s)->base)
179#endif
